All-In Platter  A plate loaded with all the goodness - Chicken Shawarma, Kefta Kebab, Gyro, and Falafel. Rice, Cucumber-Tomato Salad, & Red Cabbage Slaw on the side and a little drizzle of Tahini on top.  A glance at the spread speaks volumes of how healthy it is. Protein from chicken, gyro, and kebabs; carbs from rice; fats from olive oil; fiber from the salad.  Not just healthy, everything was delicious.  Kefta Kebab -Moist and juicy, appropriately spiced. Chicken – Tender and crispy. Gyro – The star. So soft, flaky, juicy and delicious. Falafel – Nice and crispy. Rice - Not at all sticky. Salad – Perfectly done and very fresh.  Simple, yet delicious, workday lunch.  𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐞 An ideal workday lunch spot - Quick, cheap, healthy and delicious. A no-frills, counter-service eatery. And, there are so many options to choose from. Everything from their deliciously comforting yellow lentil soup to their kebabs and smoky baba ghanoush is soo good. 𝐓𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐚𝐰𝐚𝐲 A sure shot bang for your buck. Plus, the food is delicious. We cannot recommend this place enough.

We were looking for a place to have a quick bite to eat before the Blue man group show, My daughter ordered shawarma sandwich and I ordered kefta wrap, they asked me to wait a couple minutes for my sandwich, as kefta was not ready. They took care of several other customers, and 15 minutes later questioned why the half finished wrap was on the counter....they apologized and asked me to wait at the table and they would bring me my sandwich. I paid and said to the lady “it’s ok, things happen”....I sat there waiting, now it’s about 30 minutes and I’m looking back to see all three of the staff arguing, I go back to the cashier and see that they had dumped my sandwich, I explained that I was asked to wait at the table, and received a small apology from one girl, and an evil eye from the one behind the grill... long story short I waited another 15 min as my daughter had finished her sandwich, and waited for me to quickly eat my kefta sandwich. The food was good, but that was my experience with poor customer service IDOF....it was a falafel nightmare!

Overall: Just like every other location IDOF is a solid place to get your falafel craving in "fast food" form.  The good: The falafel, which is the star of the show, has a unique flavor and is cooked to a crisp yet still tender. The portion sizes are on the bigger side, which is great for those with a craving. And, like any "build-your-own" place, there are a variety of options to make your meal out of. The atmosphere is clean and spacious for this location, and they have free wifi for those who care.  The not-so-good: The service at this location is slow at times, felt like the last time took 10 minutes from the start of the order. IDOF in general is a little over priced.  Atmosphere: 8.5/10 Service: 7/10 Food: 8.5/10
